Hungary’s Orban Plans Communication Overhaul, Nepszabadsag Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-08-26T14:44:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/hungary-s-orban-plans-communication-overhaul-nepszabadsag-says.html
Hungarian Prime Minister  Viktor Orban  plans to overhaul government communication in the autumn,
Nepszabadsag reported on its  website , citing unidentified people
close to the premier.  Political analyst Andras Giro-Szasz is the favorite to take
over as government spokesman, Nepszabadsag said. The Cabinet and
the premier currently have separate spokespeople. Under the new
structure, the spokesperson would report to Orban’s office,
Nepszabadsag said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
